Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.68,0:00:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's win.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.35,0:00:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who the heck are {\i1}you?{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just who {\i1}are{\i0} you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.70,0:00:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Astral?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.28,0:00:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember correctly....
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.83,0:00:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the heck is this guy saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's wrong, Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.12,0:00:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why are you talking to yourself over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.58,0:00:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys don't see this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.84,0:00:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.88,0:00:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, here! Right Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.34,0:00:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is someone actually there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.30,0:00:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right {\i1}here!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.59,0:00:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here! The strange looking guy! Standing next to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.30,0:00:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think... the guy's lost his mind 'cause he's scared or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.30,0:00:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Look! It's here! IT'S HERE! HERE!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.39,0:00:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am {\i1}not{\i0} afraid!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.81,0:00:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I the only one who can see this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.02,0:00:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did my D-Gazer malfunction or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.77,0:00:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like you cannot comprehend my existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.82,0:00:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.61,0:00:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My name is Yuma Tsukumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.16,0:01:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A first-year middle school student aiming to become the Duel Champion and to bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.08,0:01:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With the deck my Dad entrusted to me, I started Dueling.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.54,0:01:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, my opponent is the former participant of the National-level tournament -- Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.38,0:01:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In this urgent moment, the thing that appeared in front of me is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.66,0:01:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.80,0:01:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they're all ingredients to color each day. \NDon't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.90,0:01:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.97,0:01:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.31,0:01:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The truth is, I was lonely. Until I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.38,0:01:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lied to myself that being alone was easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.16,0:01:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My favorite books and hobbies,\N they don't seem to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.56,0:01:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You were the only one to nod in agreement with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.77,0:01:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happiness and sadness and anger and\N Do and Re and Mi and Fa and So and La and Ti and Do,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.57,0:02:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It doesn't work unless they're different,\N the harmony and the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.31,0:02:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one is exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.61,0:02:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because that's the reason for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.65,0:02:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the sounds are dissonant from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.08,0:02:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}don't give up on the strength that will get you through.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.32,0:02:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we reach the edge of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.39,0:02:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the view we see will be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.46,0:02:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.37,0:02:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're all ingredients to color each day.\N Don't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.54,0:02:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.57,0:02:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're... a spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.94,0:02:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- A spirit?\N - A spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(285,498)}"Numbers 2:\N My Name is Astral"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What effect does this "spirit" have?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.57,0:03:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When can we activate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.03,0:03:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.91,0:03:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems I somehow lost some of my memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess when I came to this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was some kind of impact while crossing through the Gate, which scattered them...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.55,0:03:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AM-NE-SI-A?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all this about your memory and the Gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.51,0:03:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must've snapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.97,0:03:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd it have to happen during such an important Duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.23,0:03:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all {\i1}your{\i0} fault, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.44,0:03:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will Yuma be all right...?\N He's complaining to himself over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just way too reckless to\N challenge Shark to a fight like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even you, Tetsuo-{\i1}kun{\i0}! \NWhy are you becoming so feeble all of sudden?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.37,0:03:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yours and Yuma's decks are both at stake in this Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.20,0:03:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he'll allow Shark to take them away...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.83,0:03:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull yourself together, Yuma!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}am{\i0} pulled together!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:04:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That aside, it looks like I'm the only one who can see this guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.67,0:04:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.55,0:04:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ever since Shark Summoned that Numbers card... \Nthe atmosphere changed all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.31,0:04:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers 17... Revice Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.02,0:04:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this Exceeds Monster appears,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.64,0:04:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my body was overwhelmed with the endless power!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I am for now, it feels like there's no way I can lose to anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.49,0:04:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take away your Deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card face-down on the field and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.70,0:04:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.95,0:04:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be some of my important memories sealed within it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.17,0:04:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My instinct is telling me I need to win this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.84,0:04:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Duel"? You know how to Duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.47,0:04:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.05,0:04:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am... a Duelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Duelist's spirit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.97,0:04:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- A Duelist's spirit?\N - A Duelist's spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.93,0:04:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Duelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's... my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:04:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}my{\i0} turn, darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:04:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will set Gogogo Golem in Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.65,0:05:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't butt into my Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Gogogo Golem in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.41,0:05:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's got 1800 Attack Power,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it won't be enough to beat his Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Unprecedented Wind, from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.67,0:05:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unprecedented Wind lets me choose one Monster in Attack Mode and increase its Attack Power by 1000 points until my next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.31,0:05:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, here's your chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.93,0:05:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.73,0:05:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Revice Dragon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.90,0:05:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it! With this, Revice Dragon is destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.78,0:05:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I've reduced Shark's Life for the first time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,YAYY!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.99,0:05:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.66,0:05:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His Life was reduced...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.21,0:06:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why wasn't it destroyed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When they're both in Attack Mode, the one with the higher Attack Power wins, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.13,0:06:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second! Revice Dragon should be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops. I guess I forgot to mention this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers can only be defeated by other Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way... I don't have any of these "Numbers" things...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.23,0:06:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers can only be defeated by Numbers? Then what's he supposed to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma: B-But, I can care less about Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gogogo Golem's Attack Power is still higher than Revice Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.20,0:06:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next turn, Gogogo Golem will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.54,0:06:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he has a Monster with 800 or higher Attack Power in his hand, we stand no chance of winning this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Life's still at 1000, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Observation #1: Your Dueling tactics are no where as good as mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not as good as yous!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What does "tactics" mean, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:07:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means "strategy"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.19,0:07:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, {\i1}strategy{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.19,0:07:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strategy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, the match is decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.86,0:07:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Drill Barnacle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,300 Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.24,0:07:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean it! What the heck are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.25,0:07:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Revise Dragon's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.67,0:07:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By removing one Overlay Unit, I can increase its Attack Power by 500!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.34,0:07:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3000 Attack Points... Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.63,0:07:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revice Dragon did have one Overlay Unit remaining,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.76,0:07:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it was almost certain that he would would use that effect to boost its Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.60,0:07:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No Way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.77,0:07:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Revice Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now my Life's 800?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:08:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This guy can foresee things that far ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.41,0:08:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still have an attack remaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drill Barnacle, Drill Attack!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.05,0:08:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When in Defense Mode, Gogogo Golem has an effect that prevents it from being destroyed in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.81,0:08:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had listened to my advice and set Gogogo Golem in Defense Position, we wouldn't be in this pinch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.19,0:08:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut Up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.61,0:08:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? My life is fading as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers....
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.58,0:08:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral: I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.42,0:08:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers... are the pieces of my memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.13,0:08:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers are special cards, even among the Exceeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cards in this world are no match for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.51,0:09:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when two Numbers Duel, the winner shall absorb loser's Numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.73,0:09:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we fail to win this Duel, then I will disappear.... from this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must win this Duel at all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.36,0:09:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I planned to win from the beginning!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.03,0:09:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I don't have any card \Nin my hand that can bring a reversal....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next turn, as long as I can survive Revice Dragon's attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}even with an attack from Drill Barnacle, I'll still have 200 Life remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.50,0:09:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking is a waste of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.71,0:09:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Drill Barnacle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card successfully inflicted battle damage to the opponent,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.63,0:09:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,its Attack Power goes up by 1000 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, Drill Barnacle is a Monster that can attack the opponent directly, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.23,0:09:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next turn, if its Direct Attack connects, it's all over for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.69,0:09:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.73,0:09:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm hit with that thing, I'll lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.07,0:09:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do... What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:09:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a Trap Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.45,0:10:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... What card did I set, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.28,0:10:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-Bye Damage, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.66,0:10:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you activate the card, not only will you have inflicted damage to your opponent, but Gogogo Golem will not be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.00,0:10:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd forgotten because you kept distracting me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.09,0:10:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's high time you forfeit this Duel already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way I'll give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, do you still think you have a chance to win?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}won't{\i0} give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.26,0:10:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I won't give up"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.14,0:10:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That statement bothers me so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.73,0:10:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do now...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.27,0:10:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.23,0:10:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To do so, the necessary conditions are for you to assemble two Monsters on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen carefully... mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Name's Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.78,0:10:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then listen carefully...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.99,0:10:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not "Toma"! It's Yuma!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.70,0:10:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for your next draw, draw a card which enables you to Special Summon a Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.87,0:10:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A card that allows me to Special Summon?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to draw that card no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.38,0:10:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh!! Shut Up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:11:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mine and Tetsuo's decks are on the line in this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.22,0:11:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resurrection of the Dead, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.80,0:11:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like fate has not abandoned me yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.77,0:11:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm{\i0} the one who drew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.73,0:11:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Ganbara Knight in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma! Why are you playing it in Attack Mode?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.65,0:11:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ganbara Knight's Attack Power is zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.19,0:11:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahhhh!!! Shoot!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.90,0:11:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my win now, so just give up already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't plan to give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.95,0:11:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just bring it to 'em like always!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.37,0:11:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Bring it to 'em"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.00,0:11:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Bring it to 'em" means having the spirit to challenge and a heart that will never give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A person's heart {\i1}dies{\i0} the moment they give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.34,0:11:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I won't give up, I won't give up"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.59,0:11:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys like you piss me off more than anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.47,0:11:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, how do you plan to stand up to my Monsters with your zero Attack Power Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.73,0:11:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've done enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.90,0:12:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had you set him in Defense Position, you would have lost any chances you had for a turn around...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Toma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.49,0:12:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use Resurreccion of the Dead to revive Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.83,0:12:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot allow myself to disappear from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.79,0:12:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I trust you or anything like that....
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.38,0:12:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Resurreccion of the Dead from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.34,0:12:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I revive Gagaga Magician from the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.68,0:12:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do by\N bringing back a 1500 Attack Power Monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.18,0:12:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, all the conditions are met.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.19,0:12:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Overlay your Level Four Gagaga Magician\N and your Ganbara Knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.40,0:12:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This... couldn't be ...an Exceeds Summon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at your Extra Deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.07,0:12:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this Exceeds Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.53,0:12:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't read its text...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.62,0:12:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.79,0:12:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers 39... Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.00,0:13:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... Numbers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.21,0:13:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct. That's the power I've entrusted to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to gamble on this now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.68,0:13:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay my Level Four Gagaga Magician and Ganbara Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.93,0:13:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I construct the Overlay Network using these two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exceeds Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.73,0:13:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! Numbers 39! Aspiring Emperor - Hope!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.80,0:13:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Drill Barnacle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.35,0:13:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HOPE KING SLASH!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.11,0:14:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awright! I dealt Shark critical damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.03,0:14:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.99,0:14:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the only trump card which is capable of bring down Revice Dragon, Aspiring Emperor - Hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.96,0:14:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Yuma even have that card to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.76,0:14:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't... I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.92,0:14:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.31,0:14:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just performed an Exceeds Summon for the first time in my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.56,0:14:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey,hey,hey,hey,hey!! Did you see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.44,0:14:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did ya' see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.48,0:14:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the fruit of my bringin' it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.78,0:14:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you so hyper about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.03,0:14:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope's Attack Power is only 2500.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's attacked by Revice Dragon with 3000 Attack Points, this thing's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so? Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.37,0:14:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you managed to Summon a Numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.41,0:15:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you are still no match of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.25,0:15:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.67,0:15:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card from my hand, Surfacing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.38,0:15:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can Special Summon a WATER-Attribute Monster from my Graveyard in Defense position!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.30,0:15:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive! Big Jaws!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.44,0:15:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, by releasing Big Jaws, I Advance Summon Jawsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.61,0:15:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Advanced Summon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.86,0:15:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a method of Summoning which lets you Summon High-Level Monsters by releasing a Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.08,0:15:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card gains 300 Attack Points for every Water-Attribute Monster I control on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.12,0:15:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revice Dragon is of the Water attribute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.54,0:15:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, the Attack Power of Jawsman is 2900!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.84,0:15:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finish it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.05,0:15:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, Revice Dragon will attack Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't Hope have any effect at all?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.73,0:16:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope's effect... By removing one Overlay Unit, it can negate an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shoulda told me right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.53,0:16:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Hope's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By removing one Overlay Unit, Revice Dragon's attack is negated!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.83,0:16:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,RUNE BARRIER!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Hope's effect?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.67,0:16:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if my attack is negated, you still can't defeat my Monsters and win!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defeating his Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.06,0:16:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only have one Overlay Unit left to use!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.23,0:16:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although Numbers can't be destroyed unless by other Numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.36,0:16:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you still receive damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To avoid that damage, Feel free to use that remaining Overlay Unit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.57,0:16:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Jawsman! Attack Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.24,0:17:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do exactly as he says! Use Hope's effect once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.03,0:17:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A way to defeat his Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.66,0:17:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I activate the Bye-Bye Damage Trap Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.88,0:17:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Bye Bye Damage, my Monster is not destroyed and is protected from battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.59,0:17:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you not using Hope's effect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cuz I am who I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At same time, when the player receives Battle Damage, the opponent receives twice of the damage I took!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.69,0:17:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Yuma only has 100 Life left.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.20,0:17:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you just activated a Trap,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.57,0:17:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can activate the Permanent Trap, Urchin Bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my turn comes, I can inflict 1000 points of damage to you with this Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.21,0:17:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, my victory is as good as decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.38,0:17:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over. Yuma lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be! Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.93,0:18:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time for you to give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet! I won't give up!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.26,0:18:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one turn left for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.81,0:18:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you still not giving up the Duel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want me to give up so badly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going by that attitude of yours, haven't you also given up something important to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.49,0:18:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you abandoned something that was precious to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.25,0:18:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I for one never give up and continue to bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you what I mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.04,0:18:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you still have a way to turn this around?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.67,0:18:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.96,0:18:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a combo in my deck that can beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.51,0:18:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Grandma...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.64,0:18:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.97,0:18:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Yuma, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.85,0:18:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my victory meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:18:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Duel meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.65,0:19:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've fully recharged!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.15,0:19:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.16,0:19:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! There's only one thing to do to beat that thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.55,0:19:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Hope! Attack Revice Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.38,0:19:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.30,0:19:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.26,0:19:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he attack with Hope, who has lower Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.97,0:19:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then activate Hope's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.14,0:19:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By removing one Overlay Unit, I negate Hope's attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point in a combo that doesn't deal me any damage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.69,0:19:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's a meaning to it, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Quick-Play Magic Card! Double-Up Chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.16,0:19:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Quick-Play Magic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.37,0:19:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my Monster's attack is negated, this card doubles that Monster's Attack Power and allows it to attack once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5000 Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it to 'em, Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.84,0:20:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Revice Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.70,0:20:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I... win?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.82,0:20:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma....
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.62,0:20:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...won.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.29,0:20:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won! I defeated Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.58,0:20:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought it to 'em!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.04,0:20:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think you'd lose to someone like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We're outta here, Shark!\N - We're outta here, Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.73,0:21:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the Numbers 17 card...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of my memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.82,0:21:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Does this mean... If I manage to collect all 99 scattered Numbers cards, I can recover my memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.49,0:21:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it! You are the best! Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.33,0:21:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think I would... lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.88,0:21:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dad,Mom, I won.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.88,0:21:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.80,0:21:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As we promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.97,0:21:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you really did return Tetsuo's deck....
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma Tsukumo, I will remember this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.40,0:21:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark! I had a ton of fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.69,0:21:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's Duel again some time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.36,0:21:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we won't bet our decks next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.70,0:21:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's bring it to 'em together!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.49,0:21:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet on the draw of a single card,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.62,0:21:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and bet everything on it, huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.87,0:22:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Did you suddenly have a little change in attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.38,0:22:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.63,0:22:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd ya think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.38,0:22:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Generally speaking, you are a Duelist whom goes beyond my understanding...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.80,0:22:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Toma.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.47,0:22:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not Toma, it's Yuma!!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.11,0:22:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.03,0:22:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's our question this week!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.65,0:22:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the two important stats for a Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.61,0:22:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"ATK" stands for "Attack Points". So what do these stand for?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.07,0:22:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today's test is hard. I can't divide myself from pleasure and temptation.
